{"parse":{"title":"The Crossing of the Red Land","pageid":13788423,"revid":855969564,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption style=\"font-style:italic;padding-bottom:0.2em;\">The Crossing of the Red Land - the saga of Jewish refugees in Brazil <span class=\"Z3988\" title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Crossing+of+the+Red+Land+-+the+saga+of+Jewish+refugees+in+Brazil&amp;rft.author=%5B%5BLucius+de+Mello%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=%5B%5B2007+in+literature%7C2007%5D%5D&amp;rft.pub=Editora+Novo+S%C3%A9culo&amp;rft_id=info:oclcnum/180701914\"></span></caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;display:none\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Author</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Lucius_de_Mello\" title=\"Lucius de Mello\">Lucius de Mello</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Original&#160;title</th><td>\n<i>A Travessia da Terra Vermelha \u2013 uma saga dos refugiados judeus no Brasil</i></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Cover&#160;artist</th><td>\nGuilherme Xavier, C\u00e9lio Costa</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Country</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Brazil\" title=\"Brazil\">Brazil</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Language</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Portuguese_language\" title=\"Portuguese language\">Portuguese</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Genre</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Historical_novel\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Historical novel\">Historical novel</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Publisher</th><td>\nEditora Novo S\u00e9culo</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Publication date</div></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/2007_in_literature\" title=\"2007 in literature\">2007</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Media&#160;type</th><td>\nPrint</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-85-7679-108-9\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-85-7679-108-9\">978-85-7679-108-9</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/OCLC#Identifiers_and_linked_data\" title=\"OCLC\"><abbr title=\"Online Computer Library Center number\">OCLC</abbr></a></th><td>\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/180701914\">180701914</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/Library_of_Congress_Classification\" title=\"Library of Congress Classification\"><abbr title=\"Library of Congress Classification\">LC&#160;Class</abbr></a></th><td>\nF2659.J5 M44 2007</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>The Crossing of the Red Land</b> - the saga of Jewish refugees in Brazil</i> (orig. title in Portuguese: <i>A Travessia da Terra Vermelha \u2013 uma saga dos refugiados judeus no Brasil</i>), is a <a href=\"/wiki/2007_in_literature\" title=\"2007 in literature\">2007</a> novel by <a href=\"/wiki/Brazil\" title=\"Brazil\">Brazilian</a> author <a href=\"/wiki/Lucius_de_Mello\" title=\"Lucius de Mello\">Lucius de Mello</a>.\n</p><p>This historical novel details the lives of <a href=\"/wiki/Germany\" title=\"Germany\">German</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Jewish\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Jewish\">Jewish</a> refugees in the 1930s and 1940s, who found themselves living in the wilderness of <a href=\"/wiki/Paran%C3%A1_(state)\" title=\"Paran\u00e1 (state)\">Paran\u00e1</a>, in Southern <a href=\"/wiki/Brazil\" title=\"Brazil\">Brazil</a>, while escaping Hitler's regime. \n</p><p>To compose this romance, the author interviewed direct descendants of these pioneers, in Brazil and in Germany.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Crossing_of_the_Red_Land&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-br